and how bts ties back to the original roots of modern kpop the way it does
i wish the media would look at bts from that angle instead of the stupid entertainment journalism approach they use usually
summary: i just watched the kpop episode of the netflix show ‘explained’ and they had a whole segment near the end of the episode...
body: i just watched the kpop episode of the netflix show ‘explained’ and they had a whole segment near the end of the episode dedicated to bts and i was….very pleasantly surprised. they analyzed bts’s fame in a way i haven’t seen the american media do – they explained why bts is so far reaching and prominent globally as opposed to focusing on the fanaticism around them like most media tends to do, and i actually learned something new from it that i didn’t know before.

summary: LIKE I EXPECTED YOURE MUCH COMFIER THAN MY PILLOW WITH YOONGI
question: LIKE I EXPECTED YOURE MUCH COMFIER THAN MY PILLOW WITH YOONGI
answer:
from this list x

wc: 659

Perfectly soft and pink cheeks led the way. Your hand felt like it was being gripped on by a space heater, each finger being intertwined with Yoongi’s own giddy digits. You weren’t as bubbly in your mind from the couple of hours spent out with him and his members within the confines of a lively restaurant. The majority of them were swaying gently every other step, but it was overall a happy buzz. 

“Am I supposed to stay over with you all tonight?” You asked as they dispersed in various directions of the dorm, Jimin shouting something about using the shower before Hoseok. Yoongi’s free hand rubbed his bangs from his face, tugging you still towards the couch,

“That would be the best thing to do.” You rolled your eyes, plopping beside him as he began stretching his back, arms extending up into the air with tight fists. “Your place is so far.” The final syllable dragged into a mixture of a sigh as he released tension in his shoulders. “And I can make great breakfast.”

“Yeah, I’m sure you’ll be able to wake yourself up to do that.” You smiled thumb grazing over his flushed facial expression, watching with glitter sprinkled in your irises when his eyebrows suddenly furrowed and he glanced to you. The pout of his lips erupted into another sigh as he relaxed fully back into the cushion,

“Well since you doubt me I guess you get no pancakes.” Giggling softly at the tone and his vibrant expression, you twitched away from him as his finger knowingly poked into the tickling slope of your hip. 

“Hey,” You warned, attempting to look even a bit menacing, but Yoongi just looked at you with heavy eyelids, and half of a smirk. “I will.” You spoke quietly, raising your own hand to flutter your fingers, insinuating a retaliation.

“Try.” 

Without a word of rebuttal, you were squealing from his torso falling on yours, arms snaking around your sides before being sandwiched between you and the cushion. You laughed at the antics, simply shifting to make yourself more comfortable under his weight. Yoongi whined as you moved around, perhaps thinking you were trying to break free, only to come into a soothed silence as your fingers meshed gently into his long locks.

His eyes fluttered shut, smiling out of view of you as you continued stroking little streams through his hair. Yoongi’s lips hummed at the rhythm, constricting his arms just a bit tighter around you– protective of the comfort your heartbeat gave to his simmering mind as he listened to the melodic beat. You meanwhile were straying your fingers down his neck, and to the somewhat tense muscle at the base, pushing in an attempt to relax him into slumber. 

“You’re staying, right?” He had muttered into the fabric of your sweater, unknowingly letting you become away of an illogical flurry of worry that you may leave by his fingertips also dipping into the softness of your back. You smiled at the warmth of his voice, and sent to quick glare to Jungkook who had peeked his head from the hallway to grin knowingly at the scene. 

“Yeah, sweetie, I want to stay.” Your glare faded as the youngest padded off down the hall– hopefully not in search of Taehyung. Focus returned to the warm vibrations of Yoongi’s chuckling. A now relaxed smile made its way to you as he lifted his head up in response,

“I wanted you to stay, too.” Your bottom lip curled in between your teeth at the absolute adoration spiking in your chest from his softly jumbled words. Not getting the chance to find anything to respond with as his neck went limp for his head to again use you as a pillow, you only listened on to the pellucid fondness dripping from his own words that were supposed to remain as thoughts, “Like I expected, you’re comfier than my pillow.”

question: Everyone who make and like dumb jokes about Taehyung are dumb themselves, these people are so shallow lol.
answer:
I mean I wasn’t here in 2013 so I really don’t know how it started but I know it has continued for so long and it really needs to stop!
Whatever I have seen of Tae he has come of as really intelligent to me the way he talks , the way he expresses himself, even in Run episodes you can see it!
And even if you don’t think he is intelligent (because yeah okay people have different opinions) still you need to stop calling him as an Alien/ 4D when we all know he is not comfortable with it!
Along with this stop calling Jin - mum or princess, Yoongi as cold and lazy, Hoseok a horse and Namjoon as someone who destroys things! And stop over sexualising Jimin and Jungkook! It’s 2018 we need to let the stereotypes go!!

and now they can't hide behind the internet
summary: About the hate and death threats against Jimin, some days ago. And those who are worried about him. BigHit acted on that now and...
body:
About the hate and death threats against Jimin, some days ago.

And those who are worried about him.

BigHit acted on that now and wrote a statement. (link) 

In short, they will file a lawsuit for “Criminal Slaughter (Criminal Code 311) and Criminal defamation (Article 70, Paragraph 2 of the Information Network Promotion and Information Protection Act).

You can send from now on to protect@bighitcorp.com your receipts of those hate comments (can be for any member, not only Jimin). But there is a guideline you can follow at the end of that tweet.

So, if you see those threats anywhere, just send them there.
